<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Small (0.5 cm2), slimy, coriaceous encrusting sponge, grey in colour after alcohol preservation, recorded both on the surface and inside the coralligenous blocks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Skeleton. Not observed.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Spicules. Megascleres: straight or slightly sinuous anisotornotes, sometimes modified in anisotylotes or strongyles (Fig. 11A), 140 (175) 177.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5 (2.7) 3.75 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; acanthostyles in a single size category, 67.5 (84) 105 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5 (3.5) 3.75 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, devoid of conspicuous heads. The extremities may be pointed or blunt (Figs 11B, C). Microscleres: arcuate isochelae (Fig. 11D), 25 (25.6) 27.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long; thin sigmas 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“C”">&quot;C&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 11E) and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“S”">&quot;S&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped, 32.5 (35) 37.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
