<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution and discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
In the original description 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut oceanographique, Monaco" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 70" title="Eponges observees dans les parages de Monaco. (Deuxieme partie)." volume="686" year="1936">Topsent (1936)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished in this species two size classes of acanthostyles similar in shape: the larger were 185-265 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in length and the smaller 75-115 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Subtylotes straight or sometimes slightly sinuous, 225-275 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, arcuate isochelae 23-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long and sigmas 40-50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long and less than 1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
thick. The specimens here described match with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Topsent’s">Topsent's</normalizedToken>
description apart from the presence of a single size class of acanthostyles. However, other authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M" journalOrPublisher="Annuario dell'Istituto e Museo di Zoologia dell'Universita di Napoli" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 62" title="La fauna di Poriferi delle ' secche' del golfo di Napoli. II. La secca di Benda Palummo." volume="14" year="1962">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sarà">Sara</normalizedToken>
and Siribelli 1962
</bibRefCitation>
), recorded a single class of acanthostyles as well. This is a Mediterranean endemic species (Ligurian Sea and Central Tyrrhenian Sea). It was found on 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" genus="Cladocora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cladocora caespitosa" order="Scleractinia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="caespitosa">Cladocora caespitosa</taxonomicName>
, at 15-40 m depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut oceanographique, Monaco" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 70" title="Eponges observees dans les parages de Monaco. (Deuxieme partie)." volume="686" year="1936">Topsent 1936</bibRefCitation>
) and on coralligenous bottom, at 40-70 m depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M" journalOrPublisher="Annuario dell'Istituto e Museo di Zoologia dell'Universita di Napoli" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 62" title="La fauna di Poriferi delle ' secche' del golfo di Napoli. II. La secca di Benda Palummo." volume="14" year="1962">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sarà">Sara</normalizedToken>
and Siribelli 1962
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
